    <item>
      <title>Interleaved Content Demo</title>
      <link>https://arindavoodian.github.io</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">interleaved-post</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 11 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description><![CDATA[
        <p>This post demonstrates how you can now interleave text and images in any order. For example, here is some introductory text followed by a single image.</p>
        <p><img src="https://arindavoodian.github.io/photos/Street/ARIN0743.jpg" alt="A single street photo" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;" /></p>
        <p>And here is some more text that follows the image. Next, we can have a grid of multiple photos.</p>
        <p>
          <img src="https://arindavoodian.github.io/photos/Landscapes/ARIN0829.jpg" alt="Landscape 1" style="max-width:49%;height:auto;" />
          <img src="https://arindavoodian.github.io/photos/Street/ARIN0743.jpg" alt="Street 2" style="max-width:49%;height:auto;" />
        </p>
        <p>Finally, we can end with some concluding thoughts or bullet points.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Flexibility to mix text and photos</li>
          <li>Support for single images or grids</li>
          <li>Arbitrary number of blocks</li>
        </ul>
      ]]></description>
      <media:content url="https://arindavoodian.github.io/photos/Street/ARIN0743.jpg" medium="image" />
    </item>

